<title>COLOMBIA: Five Colombians killed by lightning.</title>
<headline>Five Colombians killed by lightning.</headline>
<dateline>BOGOTA 1997-04-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>A lightning bolt killed five people in northwest Colombia after they took cover under a pine tree during a rainstorm, authorities said on Monday.</p>
<p>Police and municipal officials in the small town of Altamira de Betulia said the victims, all men, had been playing a soccer game minutes before they were struck down by the electrical charge.</p>
<p>Two people were seriously injured.</p>
